title: MY NAMES NOT ON THE REEF@?@?@?@?

embed.description: What is the Nautilus-themed Artificial Reef? The Nautilus artificial reef was the final reward in Ocean Week 2015. Players from all around Oceania played games with specific Ocean Week champions (like Fizz, Nami or Nautilus) to contribute one point per win. The points required to construct the artificial reef was a hefty 275,000 from all Oceanic players.

body:
why is my name not on the artificial reef when i earned 13 points... this is ridiculous. my ign is imINVISIBLE which is not offensive so what other reason do you have to deny me of this stature?
 this is ridiculous and i honestly feel cheated after all the work i did to get my name on that reef to not be on it at all this is stupid and im not impressed....{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}

replies.body: I earned like 57 last year or something like that and my name isn't on the reef :(

It would've been very hard to earn 57 points in last years ocean week event as the event ended very quickly, it sounds to me like you're talking about the 2016 event which was spanned out over a longer period of time.

If you earned 13 points this year then your name will go on the community wall (still in progress). The Nautilus Reef was for last years Ocean week and you only needed 3 points to get your name on it.

If that doesn't answer your question then have you changed summoner names at all in that time? The name you had at the end of the event is the name that will appear on the reef.
ty that does so the nautilus one is last year?
Yep, this years is the community wall which there will hopefully be more info on soon.
